*Layout*
there are 8: GridPane, HBox, Vbox, BorderPane, FlowPane, AnchorPane, StackedPane, TilePane.
every layout nest UI controllers
preferred size: every control computes it preferred size based on its content

*Padding*
Add Padding {
<padding>
<Inset top=10/> // direction=padding
</padding>
}
*Adding Border around controler{

adding border{
style="-fx-border-color:red ; -fx-border-width: 3 ; -fx-border-style: dashed"
}
}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
*GridPane*
Lay its children in flexiable rows and columns. I need to spasicfy index of row and index of colimns otherwise everything will be
on top of one another.
row hight: as the tallest control
column width: as the widest control
debugging: making the grid visible will help in debugging the


specifying the index of a control {
<Control GridPane.rowIndex="0" GridPane.columnIndex="0" >
}

make the grid visible{
<GridPane  gridLinesVisible="true">
}

aligment of the controlers inside the GridPane {
<GridPane alignment="center">
}

creating space between coloumns and rows{
<GridPane hgap="{{number}}">
}

creating space between rows{
<GridPane  vgap="{{number}}">
}

Span a control on multiple rows {
<Children GridPane.columnSpan="x"> //x = number of columns
}

changing the width of a column{
<columnConstraints>-->
<ColumnConstraints percentWidth="90.0"></ColumnConstraints> // per column
 </columnConstraints>-->
}

Align within a column (like float) {
<Children GridPane.haligment="RIGHT">
}

Align within a row
<Children GridPane.valigment="RIGHT">

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
*HBox and Vbox*
lat its children in a single row (Hbox) or a sigle columns (Vbox). Normally not a standalone layout. Will be nested inside
another top level layout.
use: normally for buttons

adding space between children{
<HBox spacing="10"> </HBox>
}

changing the width of a Children{
<Children prefWidth="10">
}

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

*BorderPane*
One of the commonly used layout for top level windows.
arrange its control in the following positions: <top> <right> <bottom> <left> <center>
every position has its preferred width and height. The center is calculated from the space that rest.
is a position isn't populated - no space is being allocated
I must nest a control under a certain position, never under BorderPane directly.
each position can only have one child. So if    I want to put few controllers, I need to nested them under another layout.

positioning a chilld within a borderPane position{
<Control BorderPane.alignment="center">
}
